        "title": "fix(discord,telegram,github-copilot,google-meet): bound JSON response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nReplace unbounded `await response.json()` with `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB cap)\nacross 4 platform API modules — the symmetric counterpart to bound-stream work in\n#95420, #95417, #95218 and the same pattern applied in #96321-#96324, #96354.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`extensions/discord/src/pluralkit.ts`** — bound PluralKit API response\n- **`extensions/discord/src/probe.ts`** — bound bot user probe response\n- **`extensions/discord/src/send.webhook.ts`** — bound webhook response\n- **`extensions/discord/src/voice-message.ts`** — bound upload URL response\n- **`extensions/telegram/src/telegram-ingress-worker.runtime.ts`** — bound ingress\n- **`extensions/telegram/src/probe.ts`** — bound bot/webhook probe (2 call sites)\n- **`extensions/telegram/src/audit-membership-runtime.ts`** — bound membership audit\n- **`extensions/telegram/src/api-fetch.ts`** — bound API fetch response\n- **`extensions/github-copilot/usage.ts`** — bound usage API response\n- **`extensions/github-copilot/login.ts`** — bound login OAuth response\n- **`extensions/github-copilot/embeddings.ts`** — bound embedding batch (2 call sites)\n- **`extensions/google-meet/src/oauth.ts`** — bound OAuth token response\n- **`extensions/google-meet/src/meet.ts`** — bound space APIs (2 call sites)\n- **`extensions/google-meet/src/calendar.ts`** — bound calendar event response\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Follows the same bounded-read pattern established by #95420, #95417, #95218\n- 1 MiB cap is safe for platform API metadata responses (chat messages, user\n  profiles, OAuth tokens, webhook payloads)",
